quote_last: Behind Chapin Hall was the official campus rehearsal and practice space building for more music students. Everyone called it he Beehive, because during school, the building emitted an atonal assemblage of strings, horns, and keys through its windows; Braque guessed that some imaginative people once likened it to the pleasant buzzing of insects.
